(firstQuint)Toric Contact Lens Performance Study.

 This is a prospective, single site, randomized, masked, crossover study.

 This study will evaluate the ability of toric contact lenses to decrease signs and symptoms of asthenopia and improve digital reading performance.

 Symptoms and objective near vision outcomes will be measured at baseline and after 1 week of wear with each correction.

